<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="192" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,968]" pageId="3" pageNumber="192">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,511,536]" pageId="3" pageNumber="192">Comments</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName authority="Araujo &amp; Vivallo &amp; Santos, 2018" authorityName="Araujo &amp; Vivallo &amp; Santos" authorityYear="2018" box="[345,567,511,536]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Scolomus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="192" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clypeatus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[345,567,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="192">Scolomus clypeatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[577,669,511,536]" pageId="3" pageNumber="192">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[577,669,511,536]" pageId="3" pageNumber="192" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Araujo &amp; Vivallo &amp; Santos, 2018" authorityName="Araujo &amp; Vivallo &amp; Santos" authorityYear="2018" box="[888,1033,511,536]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Scolomus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="192" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maculatus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[888,902,512,535]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="192">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[918,1033,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="192">maculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1043,1134,511,536]" pageId="3" pageNumber="192">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1043,1134,511,536]" pageId="3" pageNumber="192" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
because of the clusters of seemingly bifurcate setae in the supra-clypeal area of females; both also have the body predominantly green, present as well in the other Chilean species, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walkley (Andean" authorityYear="1962" box="[645,821,583,608]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Scolomus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="192" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="magellanicus">
<emphasis box="[645,659,584,607]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="192">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[672,821,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="192">magellanicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The two species can be differentiated by (1) the width of the clypeus: 
<taxonomicName authority="Araujo &amp; Vivallo &amp; Santos, 2018" authorityName="Araujo &amp; Vivallo &amp; Santos" authorityYear="2018" box="[326,462,620,645]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Scolomus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="192" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clypeatus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[326,340,621,644]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="192">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[356,462,620,645]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="192">clypeatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[470,561,620,645]" pageId="3" pageNumber="192">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[470,561,620,645]" pageId="3" pageNumber="192" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
has a larger clypeus, with rectangular aspect (
<figureCitation box="[1088,1154,620,645]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–2" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1907,1930]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,1391,1885]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,1391,1885]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–2. Scolomus clypeatus new species. 1: holotype female, head (frontal view); 2: holotype female, habitus. Scale bars (mm): Figs 1 = 0.4; Figs 2 = 2.0." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1279848/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="192">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
), 3.00× as wide as long, (vs. 2.30× in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Araujo &amp; Vivallo &amp; Santos" authorityYear="2018" box="[299,441,655,680]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Scolomus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="192" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maculatus">
<emphasis box="[299,441,655,680]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="192">S. maculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); (2) distance between eye and lateral ocellus&gt;1.50× the diameter of lateral ocellus in 
<taxonomicName authority="Araujo &amp; Vivallo &amp; Santos, 2018" authorityName="Araujo &amp; Vivallo &amp; Santos" authorityYear="2018" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Scolomus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="192" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clypeatus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1415,1429,656,679]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="192">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[151,257,692,717]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="192">clypeatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[264,354,692,717]" pageId="3" pageNumber="192">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[264,354,692,717]" pageId="3" pageNumber="192" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(vs. up to 1.00× in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Araujo &amp; Vivallo &amp; Santos" authorityYear="2018" box="[577,721,692,717]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Scolomus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="192" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maculatus">
<emphasis box="[577,721,692,717]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="192">S. maculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.); (3) 
<taxonomicName authority="Araujo &amp; Vivallo &amp; Santos, 2018" authorityName="Araujo &amp; Vivallo &amp; Santos" authorityYear="2018" box="[793,927,692,717]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Scolomus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="192" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clypeatus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[793,807,693,716]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="192">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[821,927,692,717]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="192">clypeatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[935,1025,692,717]" pageId="3" pageNumber="192">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[935,1025,692,717]" pageId="3" pageNumber="192" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
has a smaller areolet, 0.80× as wide as long (vs. 1.00× in 
<taxonomicName authority="Araujo &amp; Vivallo &amp; Santos, 2018" authorityName="Araujo &amp; Vivallo &amp; Santos" authorityYear="2018" box="[389,533,727,752]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Scolomus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="192" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maculatus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[389,403,728,751]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="192">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[418,533,727,752]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="192">maculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[541,631,727,752]" pageId="3" pageNumber="192">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[541,631,727,752]" pageId="3" pageNumber="192" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
); (4) in lateral view, hypopygium 1.55× as long as wide in 
<taxonomicName authority="Araujo &amp; Vivallo &amp; Santos, 2018" authorityName="Araujo &amp; Vivallo &amp; Santos" authorityYear="2018" box="[1301,1436,727,752]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Scolomus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="192" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clypeatus" status="sp. nov.">
